commit.message:
Remove extra wrapper types PGJson, PGEnum etc.

These were never properly documented and the problem they solve can be
solved using CAST in the SQL or by using setinputsizes.
Add PostgreSQL 11 to TravisCI tests
Add flake8-import-order to source checking
Remove unused code

Fixed broken Connection.tpc_prepare() method

Also tidy up 'import' statements and move basic PY_TYPES and PG_TYPES
into pg8000.converters.
Prepare for new release
Add more constants for PostgreSQL types

Include the payload in Connection.notifications

Now each item of 'notifications' is a three-element tuple containing
(backend_pid, channel, payload).
Change COPY example to use CSV format
Prepare for new release
If setinputsizes param unrecognized, use UNKNOWN
Remove FETCH from commands_with_count for < 8.2.0
Include all Python file in the test directory
Use simple query cycle when no parameters
Add example for IN and NOT IN

Enable setinputsizes()

Previously this cursor function did nothing.
Add type oid for varchar
Cast not necessary on null roundtrip test

Adapters, unnamed prepared statements, text format

* All data types are now sent as text rather than binary.

* Using adapters, custom types can be plugged in to pg8000.

* Previously, named prepared statements were used for all statements.
Now unnamed prepared statements are used by default, and named prepared
statements can be used explicitly by calling the Connection.prepare()
method, which returns a PreparedStatement object.
Prepare for new release
Better error messages for connection failures

Use socket.create_connection for TCP

We used to use socket.socket, but create_connection is a higher level
call specifically for TCP connections that handles both IPv4 and IPv6
addresses.
Upgrade scramp to 1.2.0
Add example to README on quoting identifiers.

Add an example of executing .sql files

Thanks to https://github.com/djsd123 for this suggestion.
Add Liedtke's principle to README
Add note about run() being introduce in 1.15.2
Fix type on README
Prepare for new release

Better error message if init param of wrong type

Eg. if the application_name is an int.
